de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.type.tree

Class TypeNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.type.tree.TypeNode

  • public class TypeNode
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents the in memory format of a node inside a tree. It is a simle data class which holds the name, the level, the parent node and a List of children. Additional it implements a method to check if a given TypeNode object is in a subtree where this object is the root.
    Since:
    30.03.2014
    Author:
    Sebastian Schulz
    See Also:

      • hasInSubtree

        public boolean hasInSubtree(TypeNode node)
        This method recursively checks if the given TypeNode is in the subtree. The root node for this subtree is represented by this TypeNode object. Notice that this method returns false if the given node is equal to this object.
        Parameters:
        node - - a TypeNode object.
        Returns:
        a boolean value.
